[{"location":"musc_config/#The-EMS-MUSC-config-settings","page":"MUSC config","title":"The EMS MUSC config settings","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"musc_config/#Introduction","page":"MUSC config","title":"Introduction","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"musc_config/#Configuration-settings","page":"MUSC config","title":"Configuration settings","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"musc_config/","page":"MUSC config","title":"MUSC config","text":"Name Description\nASCII2FA Path to the ASCII2FA (ACAFA1D) binary\nPostprocessing \ndirpost \nvariablesDict \ndefaultConfigPost \ncaseDependent \nEMS configuration \n'model \n'lforc_ascii \n'lsurfex \n'loverwrite \n'lupdate_ATM \n'lupdate_SFX \n'lupdate_RUN \nrrtm Path to RRTM files (needed by MASTERODB\necoclimap Path to ECOCLIMAP files\nsfxfmt SURFEX I/O format","category":"page"},{"location":"introduction/#Introduction","page":"Introduction","title":"Introduction","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"introduction/","page":"Introduction","title":"Introduction","text":"Perhaps some histoy and background to EMS ...","category":"page"},{"location":"installation/#EMS-Installation","page":"Installation","title":"EMS Installation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"installation/","page":"Installation","title":"Installation","text":"A copy of the contents of the README","category":"page"},{"location":"installation/#Prerequisites","page":"Installation","title":"Prerequisites","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"installation/","page":"Installation","title":"Installation","text":"Python 3.*\nPython packages numpy, scipy, netCDF4 and matplotlib\nGMAP tools in /home/common/sync","category":"page"},{"location":"installation/#Quick-installation","page":"Installation","title":"Quick installation","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"installation/","page":"Installation","title":"Installation","text":"To install EMS on a CNRM computer, with access to the CNRM Lustre system:","category":"page"},{"location":"installation/","page":"Installation","title":"Installation","text":"Get the installation script: \nwget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/romainroehrig/EMS/master/install.sh\nModify install.sh (or execute install.sh -h to get its usage):\nSet EMS_VERSION, e.g., EMS_VERSION=2.4.4\nSet where you want to install EMS: default is REP_EMS=$HOME/Tools/EMS/V${EMS_VERSION}\nSet where you want to run MUSC: default is REP_MUSC=$HOME/MUSC/V${EMS_VERSION}\nExecute install.sh. A test is done at the end with ARPEGE-Climat 6.3.2 for the ARMCU/REF case.","category":"page"},{"location":"installation/#Using-EMS","page":"Installation","title":"Using EMS","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"installation/","page":"Installation","title":"Installation","text":"Go in the REP_MUSC directory\nSource setenv to have the right PATH and PYTHONPATH environment variables\nsource setenv\nYou can manage your own namelists (namelist directory), vertical grid (grid directory) and MUSC configuration files (config directory), and postprocessing (post directory).\nRun MUSC:\nMUSC.py -config config/YOUR_CONFIG_FILE -case CASE -subcase SUBCASE","category":"page"},{"location":"installation/#Other-available-tools","page":"Installation","title":"Other available tools","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"installation/","page":"Installation","title":"Installation","text":"ems_list_cases.py: Provide information about cases/subcases available in EMS\nems_prep_init_forc_atm.py: prepare the nam1D namelist for ARPIFS restart\nems_prep_nam_atm.py: Modify an ARPIFS namelist to simulate a case described by a netcdf file using the DEPHY common format\nems_prep_nam_sfx.py: Modify a SURFEX namelist to simulate a case described by a netcdf file using the DEPHY common format\nems_convert2p.py\nems_convert2z.py\nems_convertLFA2nc.py\nems_lfa2nc.py","category":"page"},{"location":"#EMS","page":"EMS","title":"EMS","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"EMS","title":"EMS","text":"EMS documentation in construction","category":"page"}]
